ivid account of numismatics, and a spellbinding look into the age-old mechanics of megalomania.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCoins, Ancient. 0aCoins, Greek. 0aElephants in numismatics. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aafghanistan.  aalexander the great.  aancient history.  aancient medallions.  abattle of the hydaspes river.  abiographical.  abiography.  aconquests.  adiscussion books.  aelephant medallions.  aeuropean history.  ahellenistic culture.  ahellenistic period.  ahellenistic society.  ahistorians.  ahistorical perspective.  aindia.  airaq.  amegalomania.  amyths and legends.  anonfiction.  anumismatics.  apopular history.  arajah porus.  aretrospective.  asupernatural success.  atheology of war.  awar.  awarfare.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093878640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938786423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938786/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles